version: 1
display_name: VCFB-9X-000099 - The VMware Cloud Foundation SDDC Manager NGINX server must disable server side includes.
global_description: |-
  Disabling server side includes prevents the exploitation of the web server by preventing the potential injection of scripts and remote code execution through the SSI functionality.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFB-9X-000099
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_sddc_manager_nginx:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation SDDC Manager NGINX server must disable server side includes.
    control_id: VCFB-9X-000099
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      Verify server side includes are off.

      View the running configuration by running the following command:

      # nginx -T 2>&1 | sed -n "/^http\s{/,/server\s{/p" | grep "ssi "

      Example configuration:

      http {
      ssi off;
      }

      If the directive "ssi" is configured and set to on, this is a finding.

      If the directive "ssi" is not configured, this is NOT a finding.

      Note: The "ssi" directive is off by default if not explicitly defined.
    rationale: |-
      Disabling server side includes prevents the exploitation of the web server by preventing the potential injection of scripts and remote code execution through the SSI functionality.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      The nginx.conf (/etc/nginx/nginx.conf by default or the included file where the directive was configured) file.

      Remove the "ssi on;" statement.

      Reload the NGINX configuration by running the following command:

      # nginx -s reload
